    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE SPEED AXLE: SPICER - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="8">
            <title>DIFFERENTIAL</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400712">Figure 12</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400712" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400712" filename="../figg14/G1400712.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Differential Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Match mark differential case halves with punch or chisel for correct alignment in
                    reassembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400713">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400713" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400713" filename="../figg14/G1400713.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 13. Mark Differential Case Halves</caption>
                </figure>
                <para></para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove differential case bolts and self-locking nuts, and lift off differential case
                    half (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400714">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400714" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400714" filename="../figg14/G1400714.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 14. Remove Differential Case Bolts and Nuts, and Lift Off Differential Case Half
                    </caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove thrust washer and differential side gear.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift out cross shaft, pinion mates, and thrust washers (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400715">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400715" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400715" filename="../figg14/G1400715.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 15. Lift Out Cross Shaft, Pinion Mates, and Thrust Washers</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove second differential side gear and thrust washer (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400716">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400716" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400716" filename="../figg14/G1400716.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 16. Remove Differential Side Gear and Thrust Washer</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If differential side bearings are to be replaced, remove old bearings using a suitable
                    puller (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400717">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400717" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400717" filename="../figg14/G1400717.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 17. Remove Old Differential Side Bearings</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Inspect all parts, including the machined surfaces of the case half.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <para>If any gears are to be replaced, they must be replaced in sets. Inspect thrust washers for scoring
                    and excessive wear. Replace all worn or damaged parts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When it is necessary to remove ring gear from the differential case, carefully center
                    punch each rivet head. Using a 9/16 inch drill bit for the J Model carrier rivets and an 11/16 inch
                    drill bit for the W Model carrier rivets, drill through rivet heads to depth shown. Next, use a
                    rounded type punch to drive out remaining portion of the rivet (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400718">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400718" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400718" filename="../figg14/G1400718.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 18. Drive Out Remaining Portion of Rivet</caption>
                </figure>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>Always use a soft hammer or H.D. plastic head hammer to strike punch.</para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Do not use a chisel to remove rivet heads, damage to differential case may result (
                            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400719">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="f1400719" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400719" filename="../figg14/G1400719.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 19. Do Not Use Chisel to Remove Rivet Heads</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
